<!-- SECTION 3: WHAT IS GSTAT APPEAL FILING -->
<section class="content-section" id="what-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="two-column">
            <div class="column-content">
                <h2 class="section-title">What Is Non-Profit Accounting?</h2>
                <div class="content-text what-is-definition">
                    
                    <p>Specialized financial management of trusts, societies, and Section 8 companies: income &amp; expenditure tracking (not P&amp;L), fund-based accounting, 12A/12AB exemption compliance with 85% application, 80G donor receipts, FCRA foreign contribution accounting, and Form 10B/10BB audit. For <a href="/society-registration">Society Registration</a>, see our page.</p>
                    <p>For Gurugram NGOs: must demonstrate every rupee applied for charitable purpose, donor restrictions respected, and financial transparency maintained for income tax, Registrar of Societies, and (if FCRA) Ministry of Home Affairs. For <a href="/section8-company-registration">Section 8 Registration</a>, see our page.</p>

                </div>
                <div class="highlight-box" style="margin-top:20px;">
                    <p><strong>Key Terms for NGO &amp; Non-Profit Accounting:</strong></p>
                    <ul><li><strong>12A/12AB:</strong> Tax exemption. 85% income applied. 5-year renewal. Form 10AB 6 months before expiry</li><li><strong>80G:</strong> Donor tax deduction (50%/100%). NGO issues 80G receipts with URN</li><li><strong>FCRA 2010:</strong> Foreign donations. Designated bank. FC-4 by 31 Dec. Admin 20% cap</li><li><strong>CSR-1:</strong> Form CSR-1 with MCA. Schedule VII activities. Impact reports for corporates</li><li><strong>Form 10B/10BB:</strong> CA audit. 10B &lt; Rs 5 Cr income. 10BB larger. With ITR-7</li><li><strong>85% Rule:</strong> Must apply within FY. 15% accumulate freely. Beyond: Form 10 under S11(2)</li></ul>

                </div>
            </div>
